The paper proposes a method for improving the efficiency and overall classification accuracy of neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The method involves selecting different paths in the network during inference, which requires a controller to make decisions based on previous state and object category information, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational cost of neural networks, suggesting a potential focus on optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed method could potentially be applied to natural language processing tasks, as it involves selecting different paths in a network, which could be interpreted as selecting different words or phrases in a sentence (cs.CL).
